==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homicide
<hw>Hom"i*cide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>homicidium</ets>, fr. <ets>homicida</ets> a man slayer;
<ets>homo</ets> man + <ets>caedere</ets> to cut, kill. See
<er>Homage</er>, and cf. <er>Concise</er>, <er>Shed</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The killing of one human being by
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Homicide</xex> is of three kinds:
<xex>justifiable</xex>, as when the killing is performed in the exercise
of a right or performance of a duty; <xex>excusable</xex>, as when done,
although not as duty or right, yet without culpable or criminal intent;
and <xex>felonious</xex>, or involving what the law terms malice; the
latter may be either manslaughter or murder.
<au>Bouvier.</au></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who kills another; a manslayer.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer. Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homiform</ent>⟦br⟧
